 to conclude that the coin is not fair. However, if you really don’t want to clean the apartment, the p-value might be small enough for you to ask your roommate to use a different coin, or to provide one yourself!","position":{"start":{"line":153,"column":1},"end":{"line":153,"column":1}},"key":"OROHWeznhT"}],"key":"FKY2SnJtPU"}],"key":"CShH1xG4dN"}],"key":"GlgyKqKtcT"},"references":{"cite":{"order":[],"data":{}}},"footer":{"navigation":{"prev":{"title":"Hypothesis Testing for the Population Proportion p (11 of 13)","url":"/pages/m15-hypothesis-testing-for-the-population-proporti-10","group":"Unit 5: Inference"},"next":{"title":"Hypothesis Testing for the Population Proportion p (13 of 13)","url":"/pages/m15-hypothesis-testing-for-the-population-proporti-12","group":"Unit 5: Inference"}}},"domain":"http://localhost:3001"}